<p>Make sure that you can indeed get this by calculating the Riemann sum.</p>
<p>So, what does the FTC part 1 tell us? It says that if we take the derivative of this area, with respect to the upper limit, <img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=x&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="x" title="x" class="latex" />, then we get back <img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=f%28x%29&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="f(x)" title="f(x)" class="latex" />.&hellip;</p>]]></content:encoded>
