		<description><![CDATA[<p>We&#8217;ve seen some intriguing things in this course so far, and we&#8217;ve developed some clever tricks, from how to find the gradient of just about any function we can throw at you, to proving statements to be true for an infinite number of cases.</p>
<p>To some extent, this is what we have looked at so far (at least in terms of calculus, and building up to calculus):</p>
<p><a href="http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png" rel="attachment wp-att-15144"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-15144" src="http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=486%2C345" alt="Screen Shot 2019-07-09 at 16.06.58" srcset="http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=200%2C142 200w, http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=300%2C213 300w, http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=400%2C284 400w, http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=600%2C426 600w, http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=768%2C545 768w, http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=800%2C568 800w, http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=1024%2C727 1024w, http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?resize=1200%2C852 1200w, http://i0.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Screen-Shot-2019-07-09-at-16.06.58.png?fit=1722%2C1222 1722w" sizes="(max-width: 486px) 100vw, 486px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a></p>
<p>However, we&#8217;re about to see some magic. We&#8217;re about to see the most important thing yet on this course, and indeed one of the most important moments in all of mathematical history.</p>
